      "contents": [
        {
          "heading": "",
          "content": "Page is the base element of a documentation, it includes Table of contents,\nFooter, and Breadcrumb."
        },
        {
          "heading": "usage",
          "content": "Instead of rendering the title with DocsTitle in page.tsx, you can put the title into MDX file.\nThis will render the title in the MDX body."
        },
        {
          "heading": "body",
          "content": "It applies the Typography styles, wrap your content inside."
        },
        {
          "heading": "category",
          "content": "Optional, link the other pages in its (page tree) folder with cards."
        },
        {
          "heading": "category",
          "content": "You can use this component without <DocsPage />."
        },
        {
          "heading": "category",
          "content": "Demo:"
        },
        {
          "heading": "full-mode",
          "content": "To extend the page to fill up all available space, pass full to the page component.\nThis will force TOC to be shown as a popover."
        },
        {
          "heading": "table-of-contents",
          "content": "An overview of all the headings in your article, it requires an array of headings."
        },
        {
          "heading": "table-of-contents",
          "content": "For Markdown and MDX documents, You can obtain it using the\nTOC Utility. Content sources like Fumadocs MDX offer this out-of-the-box."
        },
        {
          "heading": "table-of-contents",
          "content": "Customise or disable TOC from your documentation with the tableOfContent option."
        },
        {
          "heading": "style",
          "content": "You can choose another style for TOC, like clerk inspired by https://clerk.com:"
        },
        {
          "heading": "popover-mode",
          "content": "On smaller devices, it is shown on a popover instead.\nCustomise it with the tableOfContentPopover option."
        },
        {
          "heading": "last-updated-time",
          "content": "Display last updated time of the page."
        },
        {
          "heading": "last-updated-time",
          "content": "Since you might have different version controls (e.g. Github) or it's from\nremote sources like Sanity, Fumadocs UI doesn't display the last updated time by\ndefault."
        },
        {
          "heading": "last-updated-time",
          "content": "For Github hosted documents, you can use\nthe getGithubLastEdit utility."
        },
        {
          "heading": "last-updated-time",
          "content": "You can also specify the last updated time of documents (e.g. using frontmatter).\nDon't forget to update the schema type on Fumadocs MDX first."
        },
        {
          "heading": "edit-on-github",
          "content": "Add \"Edit on GitHub\" button to the page."
        },
        {
          "heading": "footer",
          "content": "Footer is a navigation element that has two buttons to jump to the next and previous pages. When not specified, it shows the neighbour pages found from page tree."
        },
        {
          "heading": "footer",
          "content": "Customise the footer with the footer option."
        },
        {
          "heading": "breadcrumb",
          "content": "A navigation element, shown only when user is navigating in folders."
        },
        {
          "heading": "mdx-page",
          "content": "In conjunction of Fumadocs MDX, you may create a page.mdx file and add the following."
        },
        {
          "heading": "mdx-page",
          "content": "This creates a page with MDX, with proper typography styles applied."
        }
      ],
